<br>
Since neither AE taunt nor Regular taunt has shown to actually generate aggro, only to assume pre-generaed aggro, I'd say &quot;no it doesn't count towards the generation of aggro&quot;.<br>
<br>
If I AE taunted an incoming mob, I can guarantee that it would beeline to the first person to do something to it after that.   AE taunt is remarkable and 100% reliable for regaining lost aggro, particularly mid fight, you can do *nothing* for 10 mins, walk up hit AE taunt and assume everyone's aggro, but the less done to the mob, the less effective AE taunt is.    <br>
