Youre wrong. We ARE supposed to be THE BEST tanks in the game. Hands down. Period. Hybrids, meaning SKs and Paladins are second placers. They should have a higher DPS and weaker defense and less HPs to make up for the fact that they have spells. <br>
<br>
No matter how you cut it, you cannot get around the fact that they GAVE UP the ability to be the best tank in the game for spells. Or at least they were supposed to give that up. Lately it hasnt been so. So they are basically warirors with spells. Theres no price to be paid for having snap aggro via spell casting. Warriors are the base tank class, and therefore we should have SOMETHING over the other tank classes. We currently do not.<br>
<br>
Verant screwed this game up from day one in my opinion by making hybrid classes as startable classes. They should have started with the basic three classes and then allowed players to develop off of that. Hybrid classes like Prelates, Dark Knights, Crusaders, Paladins, etc are always a step above warriors in lore. They are an expansion of the warrior class. Like if a warrior gains so much exp, or does some sort of deed, be it good or bad, he can become one of these types of classes. <br>
<br>
Verant decided to make them all seperate, with the idea that warriors should be the main tanking class with the most HPs, best AC, best armor, and the ability to train in every type of melee weapon and melee style. But times have changed. You can sit there and roll over and sigh and just accept the fact that some Paladin can hold taunt flawlessly, meanwhile Verant tells YOU that it would unbalance the game to allow YOU to do it. Makes sense doesnt it? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/zummy2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedaddio>TheDaddio</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/03 2:55:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3013.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Idea for Hate Generating Skill...</span><hr size=1> I think you misread my post. Warriors are hands down the best tanking class in the game, we have the most hp/ac and defensive disciplines to boot. As a drawback for being the best tanking class in the game, we do not have the same agro capabilities as other classes, this is what keeps the classes balanced. If warriors have incredible agro, highest ac/hp, and defensive disciplines don't you think we'd be a little overpowered?<br>
<br>
No hybrid is going to tank the endgame mobs whom have insane dps, but they should have a place tanking some mobs with unique abilities that make hybrids actually useful on raids.<br>
Our bonus is our defensive disciplines, our innate hp and our high hp/ac gear. It's not our agro. We ARE better at tanking mobs, we just cant grab agro as quickly, its a tradeoff and its easily made up for with high-end weapons.<br>
<br>
Just because they have some limited spells doesn't mean they should be useless tanking any mob in comparison to a warrior. Every class has a role, as it stands now it's the hybrid's job to tank some raid mobs with unique abilities where spell agro is necessary (slows, agro debuffs.) Their abilities just happen to benefit single groups more than ours.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I have no issues with agro. While the very best weapons may be beyond the reach for many warriors, an ability like this would make the endgame warriors WAY overpowered.<br>
